name: Atmosphere Models
description: Models of planetary atmospheres, including 1D and 3D structure and dynamics models, chemistry, cloud models, etc.

name: Data Reduction Tools
description: Tools to reduce primary data products (e.g. images) to secondary data products, including time series, photometry/spectra, etc.

name: Data Visualization Tools
description: Tools to visualize planetary data. Includes elements such as graphs, charts, and maps.

name: Formation and Dynamics Tools
description: Tools and models to determine the orbital architecture and behavior of planetary systems e.g. orbital integrators, astrometric/RV orbit determinations, transit-timing variations.

name: Hardware Control & Optimization
description: Tools that model and control hardware performance. For example, algorithms that perform adaptive optics optimization, wavefront sensing and control, segment phasing, etc.

name: Interior Models
description: Models of planetary interiors, including mass/radius, interior thermochemistry, interior/surface evolution, etc.

name: Model-Fitting Tools
description: Tools to fit models to data products, including light-curve fitting, spectral retrieval, etc.

name: Observatory/Instrument Models
description: Models of simulated output for specific observatories or instruments, including observatory science yields, simulated data from specific instruments, etc. (occurrence rates)

name: Population Simulations and Catalogs
description: Tools and models to simulate and fit exoplanet populations, occurrence rates, and system architectures.

name: Radiative Transfer Tools
description: Tools used to produce simulated observations, including opacity information, spectral simulators, etc.

name: Stellar Models and Catalogs
description: Models of stellar output, including radiation, particles, and time-dependent models.
